<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!-- Animation Menu - can add/remove animations without recompiling, just edit this xml file. (need to update on server and client ModuleData and change maps (restart behavior))
    menu_category is the title for the animations in gui
        [display_name] is what shows in the menu
        [id] if u want to find the node, not really used
        you can add new cateogories as needed
    menu_subcategory is optional, it just adds an extra layer in the menu to organize animations
        [display_name] is what shows in the menu
        [id] if u want to find the node, not really used
        can have as many or as little subcategories as you want, or none at all.
        also subcategories can be nested if you want even more layers of organization
    menu_item is the actual animation, you can add as many as you want
        [action_type] can be found in the module_data files, from native
        [display_name] can be whatever you want, it is what shows up in the menu
        [action_channel] is optional, if not specified it defaults to 1. 0 is full body, 1 is upper body?
            some animations will only work on certain channels.
            if 0 its disabled on mounts and should also have movement_cancels = true
        [movement_cancels] is optional, if true the animation stops when the player tries to move
        [mount_required] is optional, if true the animation only available while mounted
        [only_on_foot] is optional, if true the animation only available while on foot
-->
